edu.biu.scapi.primitives.dlog.openSSL
Class OpenSSLZpSafePrimeElement

java.lang.Object
  edu.biu.scapi.primitives.dlog.openSSL.OpenSSLZpSafePrimeElement
All Implemented Interfaces:
GroupElement, ZpElement, ZpSafePrimeElement
public class OpenSSLZpSafePrimeElement
extends java.lang.Object
implements ZpSafePrimeElement

This class is an adapter to ZpElement in OpenSSL library.

It holds a pointer to an OpenSSL's Zp element and implements all the functionality of a Zp element.

Author:
Cryptography and Computer Security Research Group Department of Computer Science Bar-Ilan University (Moriya Farbstein)

generateSendableData

public GroupElementSendableData generateSendableData()
Description copied from interface: GroupElement
This function is used when a group element needs to be sent via a Channel or any other means of sending data (including serialization). It retrieves all the data needed to reconstruct this Group Element at a later time and/or in a different VM. It puts all the data in an instance of the relevant class that implements the GroupElementSendableData interface.

Specified by:
generateSendableData in interface GroupElement
Returns:
the GroupElementSendableData object
